00:01:55.420 --> 00:01:59.620
When Dr. Maha Chalabi
approached me over a year ago

00:01:59.620 --> 00:02:03.990
about holding a conference at the
library on Tyre, I was thrilled.

00:02:03.990 --> 00:02:08.340
It had been one of my goals while
at the library to do a series

00:02:08.340 --> 00:02:12.450
of symposia on ancient
cities of the near east.

00:02:12.450 --> 00:02:15.400
So what better place to
start than with Tyre?

00:02:15.400 --> 00:02:19.190
One of the oldest cities in the
world that is still inhabited

00:02:19.190 --> 00:02:22.060
and perhaps still inhabited
by some of the descendants

00:02:22.060 --> 00:02:24.330
of the original denizens.

00:02:24.330 --> 00:02:28.840
What better place to start than
with a Phoenician civilization

00:02:28.840 --> 00:02:33.050
that gave the world its
first phonetic alphabet,

00:02:33.050 --> 00:02:37.600
without which there would be no
books, there would be no libraries.

00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:41.870
At least not in the
form that we know today.

00:02:41.870 --> 00:02:44.840
Let me conclude with a quote from
the introduction to the catalog

00:02:44.840 --> 00:02:48.660
of the most important exhibition
on Phoenicians ever held.

00:02:48.660 --> 00:02:54.460
It was held in the Palazzo
Grassi Museum in Venice in 1988.

00:02:54.460 --> 00:02:58.510
This quote could apply
to our symposium today.

00:02:58.510 --> 00:03:04.380
The conveners of the conference
wrote, "It is not our intention

00:03:04.380 --> 00:03:08.370
to present merely documentary
evidence and with that carry

00:03:08.370 --> 00:03:12.070
out a work of diffusion and
burgeoning of knowledge.

00:03:12.070 --> 00:03:15.040
We believe that reproposing
the splendor

00:03:15.040 --> 00:03:19.310
of this distant civilization
means a return to the continuity

00:03:19.310 --> 00:03:23.340
of a culture which is
deeply Mediterranean.

00:03:23.340 --> 00:03:25.960
Certainly civilization is progress.

00:03:25.960 --> 00:03:29.420
It is continual modification,
permanent advancement.

00:03:29.420 --> 00:03:34.050
But we cannot act in the present
without an awareness of our roots

00:03:34.050 --> 00:03:37.470
that penetrate deeply
into the past."

