01:01:32.540 --> 01:01:35.710
which is a pottery
remain, pottery base.

01:01:35.710 --> 01:01:39.510
And he will describe it for us.

01:01:39.510 --> 01:02:01.120
[ Speaking French ]

01:02:01.120 --> 01:02:04.350
&gt;&gt; So the second phase
is the bronze age period,

01:02:04.350 --> 01:02:06.460
the early bronze age period.

01:02:06.460 --> 01:02:12.230
Which fits together with the
ancient Greek historian Herodotus

01:02:12.230 --> 01:02:21.510
and it dates back to
the year 2750 BC.

01:02:21.510 --> 01:02:37.040
[ Speaking French ]

01:02:37.040 --> 01:02:41.270
&gt;&gt; So an archeological
trench was dug

01:02:41.270 --> 01:02:55.170
that reveals these various phases
from the 1970's that goes back

01:02:55.170 --> 01:02:58.510
to the third millennium BC.

01:02:58.510 --> 01:03:12.730
[ Speaking French ]

01:03:12.730 --> 01:03:16.890
&gt;&gt; In that period, Tyre begins
to develop its urban character

01:03:16.890 --> 01:03:25.510
and it has two main ports, an
Egyptian one and a Phoenician one.

01:03:25.510 --> 01:03:42.140
[ Speaking French ]

01:03:42.140 --> 01:03:47.140
&gt;&gt; There is an inscription in
Ebla in Syria in the site known

01:03:47.140 --> 01:03:56.510
as [French name] and it
dates to the year 2300 BC.

01:03:56.510 --> 01:04:30.040
[ Speaking French ]

01:04:30.040 --> 01:04:32.550
&gt;&gt; So the next phase
that we're moving

01:04:32.550 --> 01:04:37.370
to is the middle bronze
age, the new bronze age.

01:04:37.370 --> 01:04:42.200
Which indicates that in the second
millennium BC there was an invasion

01:04:42.200 --> 01:04:46.140
of Amorites in Tyre.

01:04:46.140 --> 01:04:48.210
Which indicated that
the city was plundered

01:04:48.210 --> 01:04:53.510
and attacked heavily
by the Amorites.

01:04:53.510 --> 01:05:05.190
[ Speaking French ]

01:05:05.190 --> 01:05:10.340
&gt;&gt; After the departure of the
Amorites, the city of Tyre

01:05:10.340 --> 01:05:18.510 position:56%
and especially the port goes through
a peaceful phase of existence.

01:05:18.510 --> 01:05:26.310
[ Speaking French ]

01:05:26.310 --> 01:05:31.500
&gt;&gt; So the third phase
is the late bronze age,

01:05:31.500 --> 01:05:37.510
which is in the 15th century BC.

01:05:37.510 --> 01:05:58.040
[ Speaking French ]

01:05:58.040 --> 01:06:04.370 position:56%
&gt;&gt; So during that period in the 15th
century we have an Egyptian invasion

01:06:04.370 --> 01:06:13.510 position:56%
that begins and several phases of it
and they last for several centuries.

01:06:13.510 --> 01:06:31.130
[ Speaking French ]

01:06:31.130 --> 01:06:36.990
&gt;&gt; So during this phase there is
evidence of a continuous change

01:06:36.990 --> 01:06:44.090
in the life of Tyre between
a peaceful and a war phase.

01:06:44.090 --> 01:06:49.600
And in [French name] there is
evidence on tablets of the life

01:06:49.600 --> 01:06:52.560
of the correspondence that
took place between Tyre

01:06:52.560 --> 01:06:57.510
and this other city in Syria.

01:06:57.510 --> 01:07:06.050
[ Speaking French ]

01:07:06.050 --> 01:07:12.110
&gt;&gt; The next phase is the early iron
age which is right at the beginning

01:07:12.110 --> 01:07:19.510
of the invasion of the sea
people in the year 1200 BC.

01:07:19.510 --> 01:07:28.040
[ Speaking French ]

01:07:28.040 --> 01:07:34.480
&gt;&gt; The local people will begin
to develop an incredible economy

01:07:34.480 --> 01:07:39.240
and this would be the golden
age of the Phoenicians.

01:07:44.510 --> 01:08:03.220
[ Speaking French ]

01:08:03.220 --> 01:08:09.150
&gt;&gt; The dominance of Tyre in the
year 1000 BC rises to such a degree

01:08:09.150 --> 01:08:14.590
that it expands towards Sidon and
there's a fusion between the cities

01:08:14.590 --> 01:08:21.510
and Tyre dominates the
coast in that region.

01:08:21.510 --> 01:08:32.060
[ Speaking French ]

01:08:32.060 --> 01:08:39.560
&gt;&gt; So we move towards the 7th
century where there is an invasion

01:08:39.560 --> 01:08:46.510
on [French name] on Tyre
with remains in Tyre itself.

01:08:46.510 --> 01:09:09.140
[ Speaking French ]

01:09:09.140 --> 01:09:11.160
&gt;&gt; And then we have the
Persians who invade the region

01:09:11.160 --> 01:09:12.830
and invade Tyre in
the 6th century BC.

01:09:12.830 --> 01:09:14.630
And leave their traces
all the way down to Egypt.

01:09:14.630 --> 01:09:36.040
[ Speaking French ]

01:09:36.040 --> 01:09:39.790
&gt;&gt; So we move towards the Greek
period, the 5th century BC,

01:09:39.790 --> 01:09:44.300
the 4th century BC until we reach
the phase of Alexander the Great,

01:09:44.300 --> 01:09:49.240
who besieged the city of six
months and it took him six months

01:09:49.240 --> 01:09:55.510
to be able to take
Tyre, to take the city.

01:09:55.510 --> 01:10:11.580
[ Speaking French ]

01:10:11.580 --> 01:10:14.380
&gt;&gt; And then we move
towards the Roman period

01:10:14.380 --> 01:10:19.400
where Tyre becomes very
prosperous with the Pax Ramona.

01:10:19.400 --> 01:10:25.960
And during that phase Tyre
adopts urban characteristics

01:10:25.960 --> 01:10:32.850
of a Roman city, including
a hippodrome, an aqua duct,

01:10:32.850 --> 01:10:36.510
theater and so on and so forth.

01:10:36.510 --> 01:11:00.040
[ Speaking French ]

01:11:00.040 --> 01:11:02.860
&gt;&gt; And we move then to
the early medieval phase

01:11:02.860 --> 01:11:07.780
to the Byzantine phase, where the
economy of Tyre continues to rise.

01:11:07.780 --> 01:11:13.280
And it becomes a very important
port for the city of Damascus

01:11:13.280 --> 01:11:18.510
and there's a very strong
connection between both cities.

01:11:18.510 --> 01:11:39.310
[ Speaking French ]

01:11:39.310 --> 01:11:44.310
&gt;&gt; During the Crusader Period,
we have an increase in the rise

01:11:44.310 --> 01:11:49.860 position:56%
of the prosperity of Tyre and there
are 93 villages surrounding the city

01:11:49.860 --> 01:11:54.080
and there is a Byzantine
church that was built there.

01:11:54.080 --> 01:11:58.230
And the port itself becomes a
very important strategic location

01:11:58.230 --> 01:12:04.510
for the crusaders in communication
with their original homeland.

01:12:04.510 --> 01:12:20.580
[ Speaking French ]

01:12:20.580 --> 01:12:26.470
&gt;&gt; And by the end of the
Crusader Period, in the year 1291,

01:12:26.470 --> 01:12:32.640
we have the expelling of
the crusaders and arrival

01:12:32.640 --> 01:12:34.850
of the Arabs, who take
