01:16:07.420 --> 01:16:11.430
Speaking of the Phoenician
African diffusion that I was asked

01:16:11.430 --> 01:16:17.270
to do is a huge subject that could
well have occupied the whole day.

01:16:17.270 --> 01:16:22.070
So I will only be able to give a
few insights on this phenomenon.

01:16:22.070 --> 01:16:27.960
The diffusion of the
Phoenicians is well known.

01:16:27.960 --> 01:16:30.770
We are used to speaking
of the Phoenicians

01:16:30.770 --> 01:16:34.030
as the inventers of the alphabet.

01:16:34.030 --> 01:16:36.190
The subject of this
naturally takes place

01:16:36.190 --> 01:16:39.150
in a series of talks about Tyre.

01:16:39.150 --> 01:16:46.120
But I need first to give some
details on how I see this issue.

01:16:46.120 --> 01:16:50.300
The alphabetic system was invented

01:16:50.300 --> 01:16:53.780
in the northwest [inaudible]
somewhere between Egypt

01:16:53.780 --> 01:16:58.870
and [inaudible] in the middle
of the second millennium BC.

01:16:58.870 --> 01:17:01.200
The exact place, time

01:17:01.200 --> 01:17:05.660
and circumstances are still
objectively questioned.

01:17:05.660 --> 01:17:12.310 position:56%
But anyway, it is a period before
what we call Phoenician engineering.

01:17:12.310 --> 01:17:15.840
And in the span of
time and evolution,

01:17:15.840 --> 01:17:20.780
took place before we can call
the oldest properly Phoenician

01:17:20.780 --> 01:17:26.800
inscription, that is the
royal inscription of Byblos.

01:17:26.800 --> 01:17:29.320
One is that of Elabal.

01:17:29.320 --> 01:17:32.830
It's a good representation.

01:17:32.830 --> 01:17:40.100
You have the Phoenician
inscription around the [inaudible].

01:17:40.100 --> 01:17:44.880 position:56%
Here I will use this inscription as
a starting point and I will not take

01:17:44.880 --> 01:17:46.770
into account the diffusion

01:17:46.770 --> 01:17:50.930
of the alphabetic script
before the first millennium BC.

01:17:50.930 --> 01:17:56.110
That is for example south Arabian
branch of the alphabet tree.

01:17:57.780 --> 01:18:02.010
The second point I wanted
to stress is the meaning

01:18:02.010 --> 01:18:05.060
and purpose of this diffusion.

01:18:05.060 --> 01:18:07.890
And of the form it took.

01:18:07.890 --> 01:18:12.220
What is clear is that purpose
of the inventor or inventors

01:18:12.220 --> 01:18:18.560
of the alphabet was to conduct
local exchange without translation

01:18:18.560 --> 01:18:26.530 position:56%
and convey local myth and literature
in their own language and script.

01:18:26.530 --> 01:18:30.460
In a region where Egyptian
and Acadian languages

01:18:30.460 --> 01:18:33.950
and scripts had been
used for centuries,

01:18:33.950 --> 01:18:37.060
it was a question of identity.

01:18:37.060 --> 01:18:40.800
Which was the origin of
the invention and use

01:18:40.800 --> 01:18:43.360
of the alphabetic script.

01:18:43.360 --> 01:18:48.070
Language as the expression
of a culture.

01:18:48.070 --> 01:18:53.030
But also of a collective
identity of a group.

01:18:53.030 --> 01:19:01.690
The diffusion of the
Phoenician alphabet witnesses the

01:19:01.690 --> 01:19:03.280
same phenomenon.

01:19:03.280 --> 01:19:08.100
It can be interpreted in terms
of promotion of identities,

01:19:08.100 --> 01:19:11.620
but also of meeting of cultures.

01:19:11.620 --> 01:19:17.350
It is this phenomenon that I will
illustrate through three issues.

01:19:17.350 --> 01:19:22.550
First, diffusion of Phoenician
writing outside Phoenicia.

01:19:22.550 --> 01:19:28.770
Second the question of
bilingualism and bigraphism,

01:19:28.770 --> 01:19:31.480
writing with two scripts.

01:19:31.480 --> 01:19:35.520
And then the birth of
new alphabets stemming

01:19:35.520 --> 01:19:38.300
from the Phoenician alphabet.

01:19:39.570 --> 01:19:46.390
So first, diffusion of Phoenician
writing outside Phoenicia.

01:19:46.390 --> 01:19:50.090
When speaking of the expansion
of the Phoenician world,

01:19:50.090 --> 01:19:53.340
people only think of
the Mediterranean area.

01:19:53.340 --> 01:20:00.280
But this expansion went all around
Phoenicia and it can be illustrated

01:20:00.280 --> 01:20:06.850
with these inscriptions made
by Phoenicians or by others.

01:20:06.850 --> 01:20:11.110
And my first example will be
this inscription in Gingerly

01:20:11.110 --> 01:20:15.380
from the 9th century
in the Luwian world.

01:20:15.380 --> 01:20:16.820
A local king.

01:20:16.820 --> 01:20:20.820
So it's south of modern Turkey.

01:20:20.820 --> 01:20:26.230
A local king of the
culture [inaudible] culture.

01:20:26.230 --> 01:20:31.430
And the local king with
the Luwian [inaudible].

01:20:31.430 --> 01:20:38.300
It's a witness of the adoption of
the Phoenician language and script.

01:20:38.300 --> 01:20:42.710
The inscription is in Phoenician
language and Phoenician script.

01:20:42.710 --> 01:20:46.450
Probably for questions of prestige.

01:20:46.450 --> 01:20:50.710
A local language in script existed

01:20:50.710 --> 01:20:56.150
and we will see it,
but was not used there.

01:20:56.150 --> 01:21:03.880 position:56%
So we are still wondering why this
king did write in Phoenician and not

01:21:03.880 --> 01:21:09.460
in his local language and script.

01:21:09.460 --> 01:21:16.340
A totally different
example is this seal

01:21:16.340 --> 01:21:21.210
with Phoenician --
as shown by his name.

01:21:21.210 --> 01:21:27.470
And this seal was found
in Khorsabad, Assyria.

01:21:27.470 --> 01:21:31.870
It shows the presence of
a Phoenician individual

01:21:31.870 --> 01:21:37.210
of very high rank in
society having his own seal.

01:21:37.210 --> 01:21:41.870
It was found underneath a
[inaudible] in Khorsabad.

01:21:41.870 --> 01:21:46.530
And was probably not lost
accidentally but put intentionally

01:21:46.530 --> 01:21:51.310
as a trace of the presence
of the owner.

01:21:51.310 --> 01:21:55.000
So here it's really
Phoenician script done

01:21:55.000 --> 01:21:58.360 position:56%
by a Phoenician and left in Assyria.

01:21:58.360 --> 01:22:05.880
This diffusion of Phoenician script
went through the Mediterranean.

01:22:05.880 --> 01:22:13.630
This example is an old Phoenician
inscription which attests links

01:22:13.630 --> 01:22:16.850
to the homeland with the evocation

01:22:16.850 --> 01:22:22.500
of Lebanon [inaudible]
from the 8th century.

01:22:22.500 --> 01:22:28.100
And then to the west Mediterranean.

01:22:28.100 --> 01:22:35.620
This inscription of [inaudible] in
Sardinia is a strange inscription

01:22:35.620 --> 01:22:39.450
and the meaning is still
a matter of debate.

01:22:39.450 --> 01:22:41.830
But anyway, it is Phoenician
language

01:22:41.830 --> 01:22:44.540
and script from the 8th century.

01:22:44.540 --> 01:22:52.450
And to [inaudible] all the way
in the 8th century before Christ,

01:22:52.450 --> 01:22:55.530
in Sardinia it's important.

01:22:55.530 --> 01:22:59.930
It was probably not to be read,
because who would read that?

01:22:59.930 --> 01:23:02.070
I mean there were very few people

01:23:02.070 --> 01:23:08.960
who could read Phoenician
in Sardinia at the time.

01:23:08.960 --> 01:23:14.510
It would more be to affirm
Phoenician presence through it.

01:23:14.510 --> 01:23:20.160
It was a question of
a Phoenician presence.

01:23:20.160 --> 01:23:22.580
And once more, a question
of identity.

01:23:22.580 --> 01:23:27.540
Then the Phoenician
culture was inserted

01:23:27.540 --> 01:23:32.490
in west Mediterranean
especially in [inaudible]

01:23:32.490 --> 01:23:36.150
and the culture and
script became Punic.

01:23:36.150 --> 01:23:39.520
This is a scale of [inaudible]

01:23:39.520 --> 01:23:47.100
and on the right an official
inscription of the city of Katago.

01:23:47.100 --> 01:23:55.800
This pretty variant of
Phoenician can be compared

01:23:55.800 --> 01:24:01.330
to have a comparison more speaking

01:24:01.330 --> 01:24:05.210
to what [inaudible] French
is to French from France.

01:24:06.400 --> 01:24:12.780
In this case, a link is preserved
between language and script.

01:24:12.780 --> 01:24:19.270 position:56%
So there was an evolution, but early
within the Phoenician ambience.

01:24:19.270 --> 01:24:25.230
After the fall and destruction
of Katago, Punic language

01:24:25.230 --> 01:24:28.640
and scripts were preserved
for several centuries

01:24:28.640 --> 01:24:33.330
in the Numidian regions
of Tunisia and Algeria,

01:24:33.330 --> 01:24:36.150
in Sardinia and in Libya.

01:24:36.150 --> 01:24:39.000
It was also there and an admission

01:24:39.000 --> 01:24:43.380
of local identity within
the Roman Empire.

01:24:43.380 --> 01:24:48.490
But I will illustrate it
with something less known.

01:24:48.490 --> 01:24:58.630
An inscription on an [inaudible]
found near a shipwreck near St.

01:24:58.630 --> 01:25:00.850
Tropez in France.

01:25:00.850 --> 01:25:05.660
With a name probably of the
owner of the ship still inscribed

01:25:05.660 --> 01:25:09.890
in Punic in the first century BC.

01:25:09.890 --> 01:25:12.840
What you have at the
bottom is a copy

01:25:12.840 --> 01:25:15.370
of inscriptions of some sailors.

01:25:15.370 --> 01:25:23.880
And all these words were inscribed
in different languages in script.

01:25:23.880 --> 01:25:26.040
Notably, these in Punic.

01:25:26.040 --> 01:25:32.480
Which shows that crews were as
cosmopolitan as they are now.

01:25:33.860 --> 01:25:38.020
So that was the diffusion
of Phoenician scripts.

01:25:38.020 --> 01:25:42.530
Then I come to my second point,
bilingualism and bigraphism.

01:25:42.530 --> 01:25:45.940
That means inscriptions
in two different languages

01:25:45.940 --> 01:25:47.970
and two different scripts.

01:25:47.970 --> 01:25:49.810
Here we have another phenomenon.

01:25:49.810 --> 01:25:57.130
The meeting between cultures and
affirmation of a double identity.

01:25:59.420 --> 01:26:06.630
This inscription I go back in
time and go back to [inaudible].

01:26:06.630 --> 01:26:12.400
Very near one we saw before.

01:26:12.400 --> 01:26:20.370
A confrontation between
Phoenician and Luwian inscriptions

01:26:20.370 --> 01:26:23.020
in a strictly Luwian context.

01:26:23.020 --> 01:26:25.150
So we have very big inscription.

01:26:25.150 --> 01:26:29.410
As for the moment this particular
inscription is the longest

01:26:29.410 --> 01:26:33.200
Phoenician inscription ever found.

01:26:33.200 --> 01:26:38.370
But it was bilingual and at the
bottom you have the Phoenician

01:26:38.370 --> 01:26:44.280
inscription and at the top
part the Luwian inscription.

01:26:44.280 --> 01:26:55.790
And it was this inscription that
led to the decipherment of Luwian.

01:26:55.790 --> 01:27:00.780
So here we have someone in the
strictly Luwian environment

01:27:00.780 --> 01:27:07.350
who wrote the longest Phoenician
inscription every known.

01:27:07.350 --> 01:27:12.410
Why? That's a good question.

01:27:12.410 --> 01:27:18.210
Another inscription well known,
whose context is better understood.

01:27:18.210 --> 01:27:25.550
The Persian inscription, which
three tablets, gold tablets.

01:27:25.550 --> 01:27:30.570
Two in Etruscan and one in Punic.

01:27:30.570 --> 01:27:33.760
It was in the context
of a political alliance

01:27:33.760 --> 01:27:36.790
between the king of
Chiri and Katago.

01:27:36.790 --> 01:27:41.850
So the king of Chiri made
an inscription and also said

01:27:41.850 --> 01:27:45.990
that he was a devotee of Eshdat.

01:27:45.990 --> 01:27:52.700
And then Greece was also a place

01:27:52.700 --> 01:27:55.210
where there were meeting
of two cultures.

01:27:55.210 --> 01:28:01.920
Here is a [inaudible]
epitaph of a private person.

01:28:01.920 --> 01:28:05.810
A Phoenician died in
Greece in Athens.

01:28:05.810 --> 01:28:07.960
The inscription is in Athens.

01:28:07.960 --> 01:28:14.010
So that is a double inscription
in Greek to be led by locals.

01:28:14.010 --> 01:28:17.990
And in Phoenician to be
read by his own community.

01:28:17.990 --> 01:28:26.960
But what you see is Phoenician
is first at the top and is longer

01:28:26.960 --> 01:28:28.960
than the Greek counterpart.

01:28:28.960 --> 01:28:41.510
And then in Malta a dedication
for two different cultures.

01:28:41.510 --> 01:28:48.050
[ Inaudible ]

01:28:48.050 --> 01:28:51.080
Here also Phoenician
comes first and is longer.

01:28:51.080 --> 01:28:55.640
It was dedicated by
Phoenician's brothers

01:28:55.640 --> 01:29:00.410
who wrote everything in
Phoenician and Greek.

01:29:00.410 --> 01:29:07.480
The third part, the birth
of new alphabets stemming

01:29:07.480 --> 01:29:09.690
from the Phoenician Alphabet.

01:29:09.690 --> 01:29:15.060
Either through systematic and
[inaudible] process of adaptation

01:29:15.060 --> 01:29:20.220
and innovation or through a
progressive and natural evolution.

01:29:20.220 --> 01:29:25.770
I will only concentrate on two main
branches which were very productive

01:29:25.770 --> 01:29:29.450
and gave all the main
modern alphabets.

01:29:29.450 --> 01:29:34.020
On the first part, the
creation of the Greek alphabet,

01:29:34.020 --> 01:29:39.210 position:56%
symbolized by the history of Cadmous
bringing the Phoenician letters,

01:29:39.210 --> 01:29:42.510
Phoenician gramata, to the Greeks.

01:29:42.510 --> 01:29:46.390
A Greek tradition which
Phoenician adopted on their coins.

01:29:46.390 --> 01:29:52.540
And I think we will see them later.

01:29:52.540 --> 01:29:55.380
What we can see now
is the possibility

01:29:55.380 --> 01:29:58.190
of a fusion intermediate
is now a subject

01:29:58.190 --> 01:30:01.050
of this fusion among specialists.

01:30:01.050 --> 01:30:04.970
So it goes to the oldest Greek

01:30:04.970 --> 01:30:12.330
and we only show this oldest Greek
inscription from the 8th century.

01:30:12.330 --> 01:30:17.390
What we see is that the form
of the letters is very close

01:30:17.390 --> 01:30:19.420
to the letters of Phoenician
alphabet.

01:30:19.420 --> 01:30:27.730
It didn't have any evolution at the
time for those Phoenician letters.

01:30:27.730 --> 01:30:34.760
But the system is already
a new one with vowels.

01:30:34.760 --> 01:30:37.320
That was the main invention
of the Greeks.

01:30:37.320 --> 01:30:45.360
And for example, from right to left
you can see [inaudible] with an O

01:30:45.360 --> 01:30:56.450
and this aleph already as an R.
And this alphabet was the origin

01:30:56.450 --> 01:31:03.850
of the Etruscan alphabet, ancestor
of our modern Latin alphabet.

01:31:03.850 --> 01:31:05.150
So that is well known.

01:31:05.150 --> 01:31:10.540
I will go quickly to the other
branch because I don't need

01:31:10.540 --> 01:31:14.230
to explain the Latin alphabet here.

01:31:14.230 --> 01:31:19.040 position:56%
The second branch which is also very
interesting, perhaps less known,

01:31:19.040 --> 01:31:23.300
is the evolution to
the Aramaic alphabet.

01:31:23.300 --> 01:31:29.550
Here we don't have an
innovation, a fundamental change,

01:31:29.550 --> 01:31:32.640
as there was in the Greek alphabet.

01:31:32.640 --> 01:31:36.180
It's a progressive evolution
from the Phoenician alphabet

01:31:36.180 --> 01:31:40.720
without any revolutionary change.

01:31:40.720 --> 01:31:43.800
Here are inscriptions
of the 9th century.

01:31:43.800 --> 01:31:51.150
So about the same time as
the inscriptions of Byblos

01:31:51.150 --> 01:31:53.460
of which I showed one
at the beginning.

01:31:53.460 --> 01:31:57.560
An inscription of Hazal
and the second one

01:31:57.560 --> 01:32:00.620
of Zaku mentioned in Baghdad.

01:32:00.620 --> 01:32:02.820
Hazal and Baghdad are
well known from the Bible.

01:32:02.820 --> 01:32:08.210
So this way we can give
dates to these inscriptions.

01:32:08.210 --> 01:32:09.740
9th century.

01:32:09.740 --> 01:32:15.030
The alphabet is exactly the same
as in Phoenician inscription.

01:32:15.030 --> 01:32:17.630
I mean, we can distinguish
the language,

01:32:17.630 --> 01:32:22.050
but not the script of that time.

01:32:22.050 --> 01:32:27.090
Then the alphabet was
used by Assyrians

01:32:27.090 --> 01:32:30.020
within the Assyrian empire.

01:32:30.020 --> 01:32:33.240
It was diffused in the near east

01:32:33.240 --> 01:32:36.130
through the deportation
of Aramaic population.

01:32:36.130 --> 01:32:42.160
And this fresco from [inaudible]
is very symbolic of the fact

01:32:42.160 --> 01:32:47.190
that the Assyrian empire
used both a system --

01:32:47.190 --> 01:32:52.750
cuneiform on clay tablets on
the right and Aramaic alphabet

01:32:52.750 --> 01:32:56.840
on raw material on the left.

01:32:57.850 --> 01:33:06.470 position:56%
And then what was the Phoenician
alphabet was even written on tablets

01:33:06.470 --> 01:33:09.530
within the Assyrian civilization.

01:33:09.530 --> 01:33:15.870
This from the Louvre.

01:33:15.870 --> 01:33:18.430
Yes, I am going quickly.

01:33:18.430 --> 01:33:22.090
So it diffused all around Asia.

01:33:22.090 --> 01:33:28.040
And I will just give you
examples with these inscriptions

01:33:28.040 --> 01:33:33.550
which were found quite recently
on the antiquity market.

01:33:33.550 --> 01:33:39.090
And it's Aramaic inscription from
[inaudible] region corresponding

01:33:39.090 --> 01:33:43.760
with north Afghanistan
and Uzbekistan.

01:33:43.760 --> 01:33:47.730
And it's an illustration
of the [inaudible] empire.

01:33:47.730 --> 01:33:50.550
So four centuries before Christ.

01:33:50.550 --> 01:33:57.050
And around 300 BC Aramaic
was used by Ashakur,

01:33:57.050 --> 01:34:04.430
founder of the first Indian Empire,
the Maurya Empire that he converted

01:34:04.430 --> 01:34:07.280
to Buddhism and it's
written in Aramaic.

01:34:07.280 --> 01:34:12.570
A later variant of Aramaic,

01:34:12.570 --> 01:34:20.730
this script from Odessa
diffused to central Asia.

01:34:20.730 --> 01:34:22.030
You have the [inaudible].

01:34:22.030 --> 01:34:24.930
And up to China.

01:34:24.930 --> 01:34:29.820
The very famous [inaudible] from
the 8th century written in Chinese

01:34:29.820 --> 01:34:36.800
and Syriac, so Aramaic with
what was the original for that.

01:34:36.800 --> 01:34:39.610
At the end of antiquity,
the alphabetical system

01:34:39.610 --> 01:34:44.980 position:56%
of script was used from the Atlantic
coast of Europe and North Africa

01:34:44.980 --> 01:34:48.100
to central Asia and
then China and India.

01:34:48.100 --> 01:34:56.100
And at the end I want you to
see also this alphabet coming

01:34:56.100 --> 01:35:01.150
to other languages and scripts.

01:35:01.150 --> 01:35:06.020
Alphabetic Aramaic used
in the Iranian context

01:35:06.020 --> 01:35:10.420
in the 1st century
AD in central Asia.

01:35:10.420 --> 01:35:16.910
And so that is the Aramaic
alphabet writing Iranian.

01:35:16.910 --> 01:35:22.350
Then transferred to
write an Indian language

01:35:22.350 --> 01:35:23.750
and becoming an Indian [inaudible].

01:35:23.750 --> 01:35:30.520
And it's normal in
alphabets, but it's stemming

01:35:30.520 --> 01:35:33.490
from Phoenician alphabet
through Aramaic.

01:35:33.490 --> 01:35:39.620
And last but not least, the
birth of the Arab script.

01:35:39.620 --> 01:35:45.980
With this inscription which
is also this picture tribute

01:35:45.980 --> 01:35:49.940
to a friend Eric Gubal,
because this monument is

01:35:49.940 --> 01:35:52.100
in [Foreign name] in Brussels.

01:35:52.100 --> 01:35:58.870
This is an inscription 512
AD on the lintel of a church.

01:35:58.870 --> 01:36:03.040
And it was first dated
Arabic inscription.

01:36:03.040 --> 01:36:08.650
So you just see on the
top a Syriac inscription

01:36:08.650 --> 01:36:14.330
but just on the lower part.

01:36:14.330 --> 01:36:19.160
That is the oldest dated
Arabic inscription every known.

01:36:19.160 --> 01:36:20.490
Dated I mean.

01:36:20.490 --> 01:36:24.690
A trilingual inscription
[inaudible] Greek.

01:36:24.690 --> 01:36:30.010
So with this diffusion from
Phoenician to Arabic we come

01:36:30.010 --> 01:36:34.880
to the fact that Phoenician
was really the origin

01:36:34.880 --> 01:36:38.350
of what is very important
in our civilization.

01:36:38.350 --> 01:36:40.050
Thank you.

