1860 and left Beirut the
following year on October 10th.

01:39:56.210 --> 01:40:04.270
He decided to split his research
into four campaigns from north

01:40:04.270 --> 01:40:12.380
to south, Rad and Amrit,
Byblos, Sidon and Tyre.

01:40:13.940 --> 01:40:19.830
He wishes to include in each
campaign the most important places

01:40:19.830 --> 01:40:24.750
and to survey as completely
as possible the surroundings.

01:40:24.750 --> 01:40:30.250
With the help of the French
army, especially the marine,

01:40:30.250 --> 01:40:34.390
this program was achieved
within six months.

01:40:35.770 --> 01:40:45.180
Renan started the exploration
of Tyre on March 4th 1861.

01:40:45.180 --> 01:40:49.120
He knew it would be difficult
to reach the deepest levels.

01:40:49.120 --> 01:40:55.880
The ancient city was
covered by the modern town.

01:40:55.880 --> 01:41:02.340
And he was afraid having no
reward in this prestigious site.

01:41:03.680 --> 01:41:08.660
The oldest item found in
Tyre is this [inaudible] head

01:41:08.660 --> 01:41:17.250
of a [inaudible] discovered
in an eight-meter deep trench

01:41:17.250 --> 01:41:21.140
on the location of the old Tyre.

01:41:21.140 --> 01:41:25.310
This head was inserted in the
body made on the [inaudible].

01:41:25.310 --> 01:41:30.730
See for comparison
figurine now in the Louvre,

01:41:30.730 --> 01:41:32.790
dating from the iron age too.

01:41:32.790 --> 01:41:37.670
That is 8-7th century BC.

01:41:37.670 --> 01:41:40.740
Renan wished to explore
continental town

01:41:40.740 --> 01:41:43.260
on the mainland called [inaudible].

01:41:43.260 --> 01:41:49.740
But he was not successful
in the surrounding area.

01:41:49.740 --> 01:41:58.010
At Naphid he discovered a
fragmentary marble sarcophagus

01:41:58.010 --> 01:42:01.620
decorated with figures in
the Phoenician tradition.

01:42:01.620 --> 01:42:10.510
Caesar on the lid,
mixed with Roman motifs.

01:42:10.510 --> 01:42:23.040
[ Inaudible ]

01:42:23.040 --> 01:42:27.250
In April, Renan started excavating
Umel-Ahmed, or as they said,

01:42:27.250 --> 01:42:31.840
Umel-Ahamed, ancient
[inaudible] situated

01:42:31.840 --> 01:42:37.260
at 19 kilometers south of Tyre.

01:42:37.260 --> 01:42:41.610
He found there a lot of
fragments of sculptures.

01:42:41.610 --> 01:42:44.760
Human heads, lower part

01:42:44.760 --> 01:42:51.160
of a standing man wearing a
shunted skirt, bodies of sphinxes.

01:42:51.160 --> 01:42:57.910
A throne, status throne.

01:42:57.910 --> 01:43:04.440
And some pieces of architecture,
a [inaudible] and fragments

01:43:04.440 --> 01:43:07.250
of [inaudible] as well
as winged [inaudible].

01:43:07.250 --> 01:43:14.050
Among the finds were three pieces.

01:43:14.050 --> 01:43:17.210
Dedication to the god Baalshamin,

01:43:17.210 --> 01:43:21.500
a fragment of a [inaudible]
dedicated to the god [inaudible].

01:43:21.500 --> 01:43:25.150
And there is her statue
also dedicated

01:43:25.150 --> 01:43:27.140
to [inaudible] god of [inaudible].

01:43:27.140 --> 01:43:39.260
One of the master pieces of the
[inaudible] is the floor mosaic

01:43:39.260 --> 01:43:45.830
from St. Christopher
church dated 575 AD.

01:43:45.830 --> 01:43:49.930
It was recovered in very
good state of conservation.

01:43:49.930 --> 01:43:56.260
And it was retrieved from its
original location by a specialist

01:43:56.260 --> 01:43:59.930
from [inaudible] to
be sent to Paris.

01:43:59.930 --> 01:44:08.330
Since 2012 it is on display in
the new late antiquity galleries

01:44:08.330 --> 01:44:13.630
for the first time in
its complete composition.

01:44:13.630 --> 01:44:24.370
Another scientific mission provides
the Louvre with a piece from Tyre.

01:44:24.370 --> 01:44:30.430 position:56%
Albert Immanuel Gilbreth called
[inaudible] realized three missions.

01:44:30.430 --> 01:44:40.250
During the third one in 1864-1865
he brought a stain showing a

01:44:40.250 --> 01:44:41.870
veiled woman.

01:44:41.870 --> 01:44:47.490
It was supposed to come from
Tyre, but from the stylistic point

01:44:47.490 --> 01:44:50.340
of view it was [inaudible].

01:44:55.240 --> 01:44:59.540
Two families from Southern
Lebanon played a significant role

01:44:59.540 --> 01:45:04.540
in the constitution of the
Phoenician collection of the Louvre

01:45:04.540 --> 01:45:08.440
in the second half
of the 19th century

01:45:08.440 --> 01:45:14.510
and at the beginning of the 20th.

01:45:14.510 --> 01:45:25.040
[ Inaudible ]

01:45:25.040 --> 01:45:26.420
At the end of the 18th century

01:45:26.420 --> 01:45:29.510
when he was a consul
for several countries.

01:45:29.510 --> 01:45:33.900
France, Spain but also
the United States.

01:45:33.900 --> 01:45:38.980
His son moved to Sidon in 1853.

01:45:38.980 --> 01:45:43.990 position:56%
Vice consul of Franc, he was very
active in the search of antiquities.

01:45:43.990 --> 01:45:48.070
And he discovered the
sarcophagus of Eshmunanzar.

01:45:48.070 --> 01:45:51.740
Later, he went to work
for the [French name]

01:45:51.740 --> 01:45:53.220
and gave this marble relic

01:45:53.220 --> 01:45:55.400
from [inaudible] depicting
a Phoenician theme.

01:45:55.400 --> 01:45:59.070
[Inaudible] in front of one
incense burner with [inaudible].

01:45:59.070 --> 01:46:00.750
His youngest son [inaudible]
was a [inaudible]

01:46:00.750 --> 01:46:02.870
in Sidon and later in Paris.

01:46:02.870 --> 01:46:06.990
In 1882 his own marble
[inaudible] got to be reused

01:46:06.990 --> 01:46:08.450
in the wall of the house in Sour.

01:46:08.450 --> 01:46:12.380
Five members of the family, two
brothers [inaudible] and three

01:46:12.380 --> 01:46:15.810
of the sons, Michel,
Sigmund and Ferdinand,

01:46:15.810 --> 01:46:23.190
were involved in the antiquity
market, mostly in their hometown.

01:46:23.190 --> 01:46:26.280
They didn't claim to be scholars.

01:46:26.280 --> 01:46:34.900
Their trade was a way
of earning their living.

01:46:34.900 --> 01:46:38.810
They provided [inaudible]
with small artifacts.

01:46:38.810 --> 01:46:42.060 position:56%
Glass flasks, [inaudible] a fragment
of a stone basin which is said

01:46:42.060 --> 01:46:44.410
to have been collected
on the seashore

01:46:44.410 --> 01:46:48.030
in the vicinity of
the Egyptian harbor.

01:46:48.030 --> 01:46:52.030
It is inscribed with
a Phoenician name.

01:46:52.030 --> 01:46:55.100
They also saw [inaudible]
characteristic of the Tyre

01:46:55.100 --> 01:46:59.770
with the twisted columns.

01:46:59.770 --> 01:47:04.230
[Inaudible] was led
to work at [inaudible]

01:47:04.230 --> 01:47:09.870
by the French scholar [French name]
to continue the site exploration.

01:47:09.870 --> 01:47:13.830
They found a series of male statues

01:47:13.830 --> 01:47:16.770
in Egyptian style presumably
[inaudible].

01:47:16.770 --> 01:47:20.360
Unfortunately, all headless.

01:47:20.360 --> 01:47:26.460
These figures are set against
[inaudible] except for one.

01:47:26.460 --> 01:47:29.670
The bottom left.

01:47:29.670 --> 01:47:38.710
Two of them are dedicated on the
back of the pillar to Baalshamin.

01:47:38.710 --> 01:47:47.480
One to the got El,
the other to Ozaris.

01:47:47.480 --> 01:47:58.820 position:56%
They also sent to the Louvre several
limestone [inaudible] depicting

01:47:58.820 --> 01:48:03.850
priests wearing Persian cloth.

01:48:03.850 --> 01:48:14.140
Veiled woman and a
couple facing each other.

01:48:14.140 --> 01:48:19.900
This type of structure
was unknown to Renan.

01:48:19.900 --> 01:48:33.050
And we still do not know the
precise location they were found

01:48:38.490 --> 01:48:43.460
in the site.

01:49:02.510 --> 01:49:11.040
[ Inaudible ]

01:49:11.040 --> 01:49:13.590
And assembled a fine collection.

01:49:13.590 --> 01:49:18.870
He bought in the village of
Mashuk an inscription dated

01:49:18.870 --> 01:49:26.350
to the 53rd year of Tyre and he
sold it to the Louvre in 1885.

01:49:28.020 --> 01:49:37.060
In Sour they discovered pieces
of an inscribed monument looking

01:49:37.060 --> 01:49:44.190
like a [inaudible] which was sent
to the museum by [inaudible].

01:49:49.040 --> 01:49:51.880
At the beginning of
the last century,

01:49:51.880 --> 01:49:59.830
the Jesuit father Sebastian [French
name] was able to buy some pieces

01:49:59.830 --> 01:50:01.750 position:56%
