01:50:01.750 --> 01:50:09.650
pieces which were transferred
to the Louvre later.

01:50:09.650 --> 01:50:18.970
An inscribed [inaudible] on
the right from [inaudible].

01:50:18.970 --> 01:50:28.510
And two [inaudible]
showing [inaudible].

01:50:28.510 --> 01:50:38.040
[ Inaudible ]

01:50:38.040 --> 01:50:43.580
And also lead weight showing
on one side and the sign

01:50:43.580 --> 01:50:46.790
of [inaudible] on the other.

01:50:51.060 --> 01:50:56.850
After the first World War,
official excavations were organized

01:50:56.850 --> 01:51:01.730
in Lebanon by [French name]
during the French mandate.

01:51:01.730 --> 01:51:07.700
[French name] was in
charge of excavating Tyre

01:51:07.700 --> 01:51:17.060
and its surrounding
in 1921 and 1922.

01:51:17.060 --> 01:51:21.750
[French name] conducted a
[inaudible] at [inaudible] in 1921.

01:51:21.750 --> 01:51:32.660
In the 1930's the Jesuit father
[French name] realized a survey

01:51:32.660 --> 01:51:41.950
and submarine excavation
in the Tyre harbor.

01:51:41.950 --> 01:51:45.300
Later [French name]
resumed excavation

01:51:45.300 --> 01:51:49.910
in [inaudible] in 1943-45.

01:51:49.910 --> 01:51:55.060
But at the time there
