03:38:07.080 --> 03:38:11.200
in line with the biblical
allegorical tradition.

03:38:11.200 --> 03:38:18.050
It's iconology of value stands out
as one of the mightiest metaphors

03:38:18.050 --> 03:38:20.210
of the pre-classical world.

03:38:20.210 --> 03:38:24.950
On its stern, the Free Masons'
tradition also emphasizes the role

03:38:24.950 --> 03:38:31.730
of Hiram, son of the widow, as
the Tyrian king Hiram's tradition.

03:38:31.730 --> 03:38:34.970
An architect who eventually
realized one

03:38:34.970 --> 03:38:40.210
of the most ambitious building
projects, which lasted seven years.

03:38:40.210 --> 03:38:44.900
In doing so he also introduced
the asper masonry technique

03:38:44.900 --> 03:38:49.630
of Phoenician architects that
used it as a legacy of the past

03:38:49.630 --> 03:38:52.290
since several generations.

03:38:52.290 --> 03:38:54.740
Both biblical sources as well

03:38:54.740 --> 03:39:00.440
as Judeo-Christian iconography have
yielded lots of representations

03:39:00.440 --> 03:39:05.920
of the temple and its
furnishings based merely

03:39:05.920 --> 03:39:10.330
on the descriptions
in the book of Kings.

03:39:10.330 --> 03:39:16.680
Invariably in the absence,
total absence of actual remains.

03:39:16.680 --> 03:39:21.020 position:56%
So most of them entirely fictitious.

03:39:22.590 --> 03:39:26.820
In the present paper I would
like to emphasize the importance

03:39:26.820 --> 03:39:33.090 position:56%
of the archaeological representation
from Hiram's homeland.

03:39:33.090 --> 03:39:38.130
It's time to bring this
into the discussion.

03:39:38.130 --> 03:39:43.380
Documentation pertaining to the
engineering and designing skills

03:39:43.380 --> 03:39:45.970
of his specialized labor.

03:39:45.970 --> 03:39:50.740
The [inaudible] no doubt
travelled overland.

03:39:50.740 --> 03:39:55.200
