archeological site

03:40:24.550 --> 03:40:30.250
of [foreign name] is a very likely
candidate indeed for the location

03:40:30.250 --> 03:40:34.380
with Kabul and Israel
as a halting place

03:40:34.380 --> 03:40:39.010
for the cedar beams'
transport to Jerusalem.

03:40:39.010 --> 03:40:43.610
This is not only suggested by the
layout of a fort or small sanctuary

03:40:43.610 --> 03:40:49.550
in Sidil, but as well by
the presence of cedar logs,

03:40:49.550 --> 03:40:56.760
numerous Phoenician oil containers
and several Phoenician artifacts.

